node.text:
This video is from @therealkiyosaki who wrote the book Rich Dad Poor Dad. I remember the first time I read the book, I thought he was tripping on this point. 
.
.
Then I bought my first house and really struggled because I viewed it as an investment. Every time @_jen_taylor wanted to put money into that house, it became a disagreement because she was looking at our home as our home and I wanted to see a return out of the dollars we were putting in. 
.
.
We later made our first real estate investment into storage and I experienced something very different. We invested knowing the target return, the targeted hold, and this time.. someone else paid the debt! 
.
.
So the big lesson for me… my home is my home and investments are outside of my primary residence.
.
.

.
.
#realestate #realestateagent #realestateinvesting #realestateinvestor #passiveincome #financialfreedom #robertkiyosaki #richdadpoordad #cashflow #investing

.
.

.
.
What have you learned from skating???
.
.

I’ve been hearing this from every real estate influencer and people in the media… 
.
.
That when the eviction moratorium is lifted, the real estate market is going to crash like it’s 2008. 
.
.
I don’t think this is going to happen, but before I give my thoughts, I want to know what you think??? 
.
.
Will the market crash, will it level out, or will it continue to rise? 
.
.
@communecapital 
.
.
.
#realestate #realestateinvesting #realestateagent #money #finance #wealth #personalfinance #financialfreedom #passiveincome #cashflow #invest

node.text:
It’s insane to see how far skateboarding has come. When I started, we would go to parking lot demos and if 30 people showed up, it was huge! 
.
.
Now we have skaters who have Olympic gold metals. My 16yr old self would be blown away right now. It’s going to be crazy to see how the next 10 years of skateboarding goes.
.
.
Congrats @yutohorigome @kelvinhoefler @jaggereaton @momiji_nishiya830  @rayssalealsk8 @funa_nakayama 
.
.
Photos by @atibaphoto

.
.
Most important thing I’ve learned so far. Marriage is not perfect and it’s not easy… but every time we work through the trials, on the other end is more joy! 
.
.
God had a plan for us from the beginning and it’s been crazy to see if unfold along the way! Happy anniversary, Love you babe! @_jen_taylor

node.text:
Leverage can be very powerful, but you do have a great responsibly when using it. 
.
.
One thing I’ve noticed for home owners… it’s hard to get your mind to switch from owning a home and owning a real estate investment. 
.
.
Most homeowners feel the mortgage payment every month and look forward to owning your home outright to eliminate your monthly living cost. 
.
.
With investment properties, you don’t pay the rent, the tenant does. They pay your expenses, your debt, and cash flow when done right! 
.
.
Debt increases your purchasing power and when done right, increases your return as well. 
.
.
You can always chose to not use it if your risk tolerance doesn’t support it… but if you know how, the results can be big. 
.
.
.
